{
  "texts": [
    "Since LLMs are machine learning algorithms that can recognize, summarize, translate, predict, and generate human languages based on machine learning on very large amounts of text data we can use them to help us in this task.",
    "To date they can provide the most convincing computergenerated imitation of sentences and expressions of human language, but things are moving forward.",
    "What if we ''teach'' such an LLM to ''read'' informal mathematical proofs?",
    "Could an LLM express them, or if you wish, translate them, in a way that would be accepted as ''formal proofs''?",
    "In a recent work, researchers introduced a method that maps informal proofs to formal proof sketches and uses the sketches to guide an automated prover by directing its search to easier subproblems."
  ]
}